Actress Ini Edo has spoken on requirements to build a successful acting career. While acknowledging acting is something she loves, Edo argued it’s not all games and fun as perceived by most persons. According to her, the profession requires a great level of commitment, discipline and patience.   Actress Nkechi Blessing gets lands as birthday gift     Williams Uchemba gifts wife brand new Benz     Burna Boy reaches 200m streams on Boomplay, gets honour   The screen diva, who recently wrapped up filming Niyi Akinmolayan’s forthcoming crime drama, ‘The Man for the Job’, took to Instagram to share her viewpoint on the career trajectory. - Advertisement - She wrote: “It’s been 2 weeks of doing what I absolutely love…People think acting is all games and fun… “It takes a high level of commitment, discipline and patience to get the job done…From very early morning call times to late night and sometimes filming into the early hours of the morning…” SPONSORED